\par }\pard \widctlpar\tx4111\tqr\tx9639 {\b\f4\lang1033 \page }{\b\scaps\f4\fs22\lang1033 Troubleshooting
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f1\fs20 \'b7\tab}}\pard \fi-283\li283\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnstart1\pnindent283\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}{\b\f4\lang1033 The installation script says there is something wrong with the long filenames.\line }{\f4\lang1033 
Most of the theme\rquote 
s files have long filenames, which means that the archive must be unzipped with a program that supports these long filenames. Using an old unzip program results in broken long filenames which make it impossible to install the theme. I recomme
nd using WinZip from Niko Mak Computing, version 6.0 for Windows 95 or newer. If you don\rquote 
t have WinZip or if you have an older version you can download an update or evaluation version from their web site at <http://www.winzip.com/>. If you are using a Windows 95 unzipper but you still have this problem, make sure it uses \ldblquote 
Internal Unzipping\rdblquote .
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f1\fs20 \'b7\tab}}{\b\f4\lang1033 The installation script says \ldblquote Desktop Themes\rdblquote  from Microsoft Plus! is not installed.\line }{\f4\lang1033 Having the \ldblquote Desktop Themes\rdblquote 
 part from Microsoft Plus! installed is required to use this desktop theme. To install this part run the Plus! setup program, choose for a custom install and mark the checkbox next to \ldblquote Desktop Themes\rdblquote . If you don\rquote 
t want to install all the themes that come with Plus! hit the \ldblquote Change Option...\rdblquote  button and deselect all but one of the listed themes (you must install at least one of the listed themes or Plus! won\rquote 
t install the Desktop Themes program). When the Plus! setup is complete and you have restarted you computer you can install X-Files - The Theme v2.0.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f1\fs20 \'b7\tab}}{\b\f4\lang1033 The installation script says the Visual Basic 3.0 Runtime Library is missing from the System folder.\line }{\f4\lang1033 
The Visual Basic 3.0 Runtime Library (vbrun300.dll) is required by the screensaver. The installation will continue normally after this message, but the screensaver will not work until you have installed this file into you System folder. Since this file is
 also required by a lot of other programs most people already have it, so it is not included in the theme to save bandwidth and download time (the file is almost 400Kb big). You can download this file from every web site or }{\scaps\f4\lang1033 bbs}{
\f4\lang1033  that has a Windows software collection, like the Coast to Coast Software Repository at <http://www.coast.net/SimTel/>. Since most people already have this file asking a friend or colleague for it might also get you the file.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f1\fs20 \'b7\tab}}{\b\f4\lang1033 The installation script says it can\rquote t find a certain file.\line }{\f4\lang1033 
The installation script checks if all the files needed are present. If one of the files is missing, you should make sure that you have unzipped }{\b\f4\lang1033 all}{\f4\lang1033  files f
rom the archive. A list of all files that should be in the archive is included in this documentation. If the archive you downloaded is incomplete, please tell the maintainer of the site where you downloaded it from that the file he has is incomplete and d
ownload a complete version from the main distribution site mentioned elsewhere in this documentation.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\b\f1\fs20 \'b7\tab}}{\b\f4\lang1033 The installation script says the folder \ldblquote X-Files - The Theme v2.0\rdblquote  is missing.\line }{\f4\lang1033 The theme\rquote 
s files are stored in a separate folder, and are also stored in 
the archive with this folder information. You should instruct you unzip program to extract not only the files but also the folder information that is stored in the archive. If you are using WinZip version 6.0 for Windows 95 or newer you can do this by che
cking the \ldblquote Use Folder Names\rdblquote  option in the Extract dialog box. If you are using an other unzip program please refer to the program\rquote s documentation.}{\b\f4\lang1033 
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\b\f1\fs20 \'b7\tab}The screensaver\rquote s password protection can\rquote t be turned on.\line }{\f4\lang1033 The screensaver included in this theme doesn\rquote t su
pport password protection. If you trust no one and really need a password on your screensaver you can use the Control Panel to select a (standard Windows) screensaver with password protection.}{\b\f4\lang1033 
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\b\f1\fs20 \'b7\tab}The startup logo\rquote s animation isn\rquote t smooth.\line }{\f4\lang1033 
The animation is controlled by Windows when it is loading and is therefore paused by Windows during certain parts of the startup process. This is normal behavior and it can\rquote t be changed.}{\b\f4\lang1033 
\par }\pard \widctlpar {\f4\lang1033 
\par 
\par }{\b\scaps\f4\fs22\lang1033 Uninstalling the startup and shutdown logos
\par }{\f4\lang1033 Since the startup and shutdown logos cannot be changed through the Control Panel\rquote s \ldblquote Desktop Themes\rdblquote  applet, I have included two small scripts in the theme\rquote 
s package to make it easy to uninstall and re-install these logos. Called \ldblquote }{\i\f4\lang1033 Uninstall X-Files logos.bat}{\f4\lang1033 \rdblquote  and \ldblquote }{\i\f4\lang1033 Reinstall X-Files logos.bat}{\f4\lang1033 \rdblquote 
 they are placed in the main theme folder (this usually is \ldblquote }{\i\f4\lang1033 c:\\program files\\plus!\\themes}{\f4\lang1033 \rdblquote 
), but they can be safely moved to any other location without losing their functionality. To uninstall or re-install the theme\rquote s logos all you have to do is run the appropriate file by double clicking on it.
\par 
\par }{\i\f4\lang1033 Note: These scripts only work if you have used the theme\rquote s installation script to install the theme.
